%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Pods as Training Pods<br/>(Worker/Master/PS)
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>(OpenShift Monitoring)

    Note over User,Pods: Flow 1: Training Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply PyTorchJob<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>443→9443/TCP, HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Result (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created / Rejected

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Controller Reconciliation

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: PyTorchJob created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Bearer Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Services<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Bearer Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created

    Note over Pods: Flow 3: Inter-Pod Training Communication

    Pods->>Pods: Distributed training communication<br/>via headless Service<br/>Framework-specific ports, TCP plaintext<br/>NetworkPolicy enforced

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update job status<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Bearer Token

    Note over Prom,Operator: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>PodMonitor scraping
    Operator-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(jobs created/succeeded/failed)
